Description:
The Grechko Lab at Volgograd State Medical University conducts research in:
- condensed benzimidazole derivatives as useful molecules for new drugs;
- the pharmacological effects of novel biologically active natural substances and their synthetical derivatives (purines, pyrimidines, benzimidazoles, neuroactive amino acids, magnesium salts, etc.);
- the pharmacological effects of substances as potential anticonvulsive drugs (with original mechanism of action);
- preclinical studies of kappa-opioid receptor agonists;
- the pharmacological effects of substances that are considered a potential treatment for metabolic disorders
